  "10.29": (
    caption: [The production and drainage of aqueous humor. Aqueous humor maintains the intraocular pressure within the anterior and posterior chambers. It is secreted into the posterior chamber, flows through the pupil into the anterior chamber, and drains from the eyeball through the canal of Schlemm.],
