  "10.39": (
    caption: [The photodissociation of rhodopsin. (a) The photopigment rhodopsin consists of the protein opsin combined with 11–cis-retinal (retinene). (b) Upon exposure to light, the retinal is converted to a different form, called all-trans, and dissociates from the opsin. This photochemical reaction induces changes in ionic permeability that ultimately result in stimulation of ganglion cells in the retina.],
